node.text: For the latest installment of “Invite Only”, @hypebeastjp’s @yvkiabe linked up with multi-hyphenate Poggy to chat about his latest pick up, including the @adidasoriginals NMD S1, celebratory @newbalance 990, a bag by @larrysmith_official, and upcycled denim by @proletareart.

node.text: The highly-anticipated album is now set to release on August 15. The date was confirmed by an iTunes album preview page. The album was predicted to release following the end of ’Ye’s second listening event but to no surprise no album was released. Watch our latest episode of HBNN to get the “whoopity-scoop.”

node.text: Skateboarding made its debut at the summer Olympics in Tokyo and we took a look at some of the best moments, how its spotlighting streetwear, and how the addition of new sports is connecting with the younger audience.

node.text: The new album is named for West’s late mother, who passed away in 2007. While DONDA explores a wider range of genres than his previous album Jesus is King, it features some of the religious themes that West has pivoted to in his recent music. A partial tracklist posted by West ahead of the release listed titles like “Pure Souls” and “Keep My Spirit Alive.” The album will be available for purchase and streaming on July 23rd.

node.text: Founded by Jeff Bezos, space travel company Blue Origin completed its first passenger flight on July 20. The rocket, named New Shepard, carried Bezos and three other passengers more than 65-miles above Earth, just to the boundary of space, known as the Kármán line. Watch our latest episode of HBNN to learn more.

node.title: @jeffbezos Completes His First Flight into Space

node.text: @gucci unveils inaugural ‘Fashion Haul’ episode for its new web series in partnership with HYPEBEAST - bringing together prominent figures to break down the luxury house’s latest designs and exploring subcultures through the world of user-generated online streaming. This episode focuses on the House’s 25 Eschatology styles as well as the new #GucciBasket sneakers.

node.text: Continuing to make sure that fans have something to celebrate whether they’re courtside or elsewhere, @oculus is partnering with HYPEBEAST News Network to share the top NBA-related news, keeping you up to date on all things basketball all season long. In this episode, we take a look at the new promo for ‘Space Jam: A New Legacy,’ starring LeBron James, in addition to the movie’s merchandise drops from Nike and Converse.

node.title: Space Jam: A New Legacy has dropped a full range of new merch and sneakers

node.text:
Our first ever @hypegolf Invitational in Miami took place on May 13 and brought together the best in style, music, entertainment, food, and, of course, golf. Stay tuned for the next one in a city near you.
Thank you all who came out! @remi.god @manoloteachesgolf @mattjames919 @tjmizell @williemack3 @parishilinskigolf @janetgretzky @oooolajuwon @eastsidegolf @jabbawockeez @coach_rusty @haileyostrom @holein1trickshots @stephenmalbon @malbongolf @mvegapena @adriancolbert @earldreambig
#hypegolf #hypegolfinvitational

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by HYPEBEAST on August 15, 2021 tagging @nike, and @hypebeastkicks. May be an image of footwear.

node.text:
@hypebeastkicks:⁠ @nike celebrates the @nba's 75th anniversary, with the collaborative Dunk Low EMB “Chicago.” The iconic fan-favorite color-blocking is rendered throughout the uppers, which utilize both smooth and tumbled leathers. The tongue tab displays special imagery featuring Jerry West alongside “75 Anniversary” text. As a final nod to the celebration, a diamond graphic is laser-engraved onto the silver lace deubré. Expect these to release sometime in October.⁠
Photo: Nike

node.text:
@hypebeastcarclub: ⁠It has just been revealed that @bugatti's Bolide will indeed hit the streets, with production already underway. The hypercar packs a punch with a quad-turbo eight-liter W16 engine cranking out 1,825 HP. The automotive spectacle is scheduled for delivery in 2024 with a limited run of 40 units and a price tag of approximately $4.7 million USD.⁠⁠
Photo: Bugatti

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by HYPEBEAST on August 15, 2021 tagging @bugatti, and @hypebeastcarclub.
Photo by HYPEBEAST on August 15, 2021.

Photo shared by HYPEBEAST on August 15, 2021 tagging @hypebeastjp, @atmos_japan, and @hypebeastkicks. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎HYPEBEAST NIVERSIT ប្ញា្ ن M ZESE ATMOS JAPAN LAUNCHES 'ATMOSYA' POP-UP IN SHIBUYA Featuring vintage Nike runners from the 70s and 80s.‎'‎.

node.text:
@hypebeastkicks: @atmos_japan heads to Harajuku to launch its 'Atmosya' pop-up and it's a vintage haven. The @hypebeastjp team is at the scene for an exclusive look at the space which is inspired by Japanese summer festivals (natsumatsuri) from the Showa era. On display are @nike shoes and apparel from the sportswear giant's early days, a reflection of Japan's unrivaled vintage collection culture.⁠
Photo: HYPEBEAST Japan

node.text:
@apple’s upcoming generation of the iPhone will reportedly have new enhancements to its camera capabilities including portrait mode for video. To execute this, the new feature will adopt Apple’s ProRes which is a high-quality video compression format that supports resolutions up to 8K. Stay tuned for more word on its release.⁠
Photo: Riku Ogawa/HYPEBEAST

node.text:
@hypeart: Paris‘ iconic L’Arc de Triomphe monument is currently being wrapped for an art project that has been 60 years in the making. 'L’Arc de Triomphe, Wrapped' was the brain-child of late artist couple, Christo and Jeanne-Claude, who have given full clearance in their will to have their team continue to work on this project past their death. Hit the link in bio to watch the live stream. ⁠
Photo: André Grossmann/Christo and Jeanne-Claude Foundation

node.text:
@hypebeastkicks: @nike is digging back into its archives to generate a “What The” take on the Air Presto. Each foot is executed with callouts to the silhouette's colorways of the past, including its “Australia,” “Unholy Cumulus,” “Brutal Honey,” “Trouble at Home,” and several additional makeups. Expect these to see a release in the coming weeks for $130 USD.⁠⁠
Photo: Nike

@hypeart: The groundbreaking art exhibition, 'Superblue,' is coming to London and New York in the fall. First launched in Miami by Pace Gallery, featuring some of the world's leading experiential artists, the exhibit aims to transport you into otherworldly realms through an alluring use of form and color. Hit the link in bio for more info.⁠⁠
Photo: DRIFT

node.text:
@hypegolf: @taylormadegolf has introduced its third generation of the P790 irons. To address the mission of enhancing one of the most lavish irons they have produced, engineers launched into regenerating the technology that stands at the core. The TaylorMade P790 iron set is offered in steel and graphite shafts and is priced at $1,400-1,600 USD. Pre-order on now with shipping on September 3.⁠⁠
Photo: Taylor Made Golf

node.text:
@hypebeastkicks: @nike is set to release another “Be True to Your School” iteration: the Dunk Low in a familiar “Goldenrod” colorway. The low-cut blends yellow leather mudguards, eyestays, Swooshes, collar flaps and heel tabs with black leather toeboxes, quarters and collars. Tongues are embellished with yellow tag detailing plus trim, while white midsoles team with yellow outsoles to complete the look. These are likely to release this fall for $100 USD.⁠
Photo: @brandon1an
